{"questionId":"17421","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A random variable <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span> has a distribution with mean <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mu \">\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n</math></span> and variance 4. A random sample of&nbsp;size 100 is to be taken from the distribution of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"X\">\n  <mi>X</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Josie takes a different random sample of size 100 to test the null hypothesis that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mu&nbsp; = 60\">\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>60</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;against the alternative hypothesis that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\mu&nbsp; > 60\">\n  <mi>μ</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>60</mn>\n</math></span> at the 5 % level.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the probability that Josie makes a Type I error.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>0.05&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"17421","referenceCode":"19N.3.AHL.TZ0.Hsp_3c.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the probability that Josie makes a Type I error.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.18—T and Z test, type I and II errors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}